<h2 class="content-title">What I'm Doing Now</h2>
<p>This page is inspired by <a href="https://nownownow.com/" target="_blank">nownownow.com</a>. It's a snapshot of what I'm currently focusing on, learning, and enjoying. It's updated periodically, so check back for the latest!</p>

<h3>&#128187; What I'm Working On</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Refining this Website:</strong> Continuously improving the UI/UX, responsiveness, and subtle animations. Your feedback is always welcome!</li>
    <li><strong>Learning Advanced JavaScript:</strong> Diving deeper into asynchronous programming, modern ES6+ features, and front-end frameworks to build more complex web applications.</li>
    <li><strong>Home Automation Projects:</strong> Experimenting with new integrations and automations in Home Assistant, particularly focusing on energy monitoring and smart lighting scenes.</li>
</ul>

<h3>&#128218; What I'm Reading</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>"Clean Code" by Robert C. Martin:</strong> Re-reading this classic to reinforce best practices in software development and write more maintainable code.</li>
    <li><strong>"The Pragmatic Programmer" by Andrew Hunt and David Thomas:</strong> Exploring timeless advice for developers on how to be more effective and productive.</li>
</ul>

<h3>&#128214; What I'm Learning</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Python for Data Analysis:</strong> Expanding my skills in data manipulation and visualization using libraries like Pandas and Matplotlib.</li>
    <li><strong>Cloud Computing (Azure/GCP):</strong> Getting more hands-on with cloud services for deploying web applications and managing infrastructure.</li>
    <li><strong>Containerization with Docker:</strong> Understanding how to package applications and their dependencies into portable containers for consistent deployment.</li>
</ul>

